    "Given a decorated surface Σ we let Σ be the decorated surface obtained from Σ by reversing the orientation and flipping the signs of all marked boundary points.",
    "Then ∂ Σ = ∂Σ as decorated 1-manifolds.",
    "Given a string diagram x on Σ we obtain a string diagram x on Σ by reversing the orientations of all edges and replacing the label of each internal vertex by its dagger.Let • local relations of the graphical calculus applied inside contractible disks in Σ, to string diagrams whose edges cross the boundary of this disk transversally.We call A(Σ):= b∈B(Σ) A(Σ; b) the skein module on Σ.",
    "Here, B(Σ) is the finite set of all simple boundary conditions for string diagrams on Σ.Given a string diagram x on a decorated surface Σ, we write [x] Σ ∈ A(Σ) for its equivalence class in the skein module.",
    "When the decorated surface is clear from context, we often simply write[x]."
